<subSubSection pageId="200" pageNumber="201" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="200" pageNumber="201">
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 179" captionStartId="F179" captionText="Figure 179. Distribution of Conostegia osaensis." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure179" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96537" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">179</figureCitation>
). Endemic to the Osa Peninsula in southern Costa Rica, 40-200 m in elevation.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-Zenodo-Dep="974013" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure179" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96537" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" start="Figure 179" startId="F179">
