<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Aguilar, Kriebel &amp; Almeda" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia osaensis" order="Myrtales" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="osaensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Conostegia osaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="200" pageNumber="201">
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Aguilar, Kriebel &amp; Almeda" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia osaensis" order="Myrtales" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="osaensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Conostegia osaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to the Osa Peninsula of Costa Rica and quite distinctive as it tends to be a large tree up to about 25 m tall. In addition, the leaf abaxial surface is covered with a stellate lepidote indument and the flowers are calyptrate, not pleiostemonous, and have a short style. In the molecular phylogeny 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Aguilar, Kriebel &amp; Almeda" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia osaensis" order="Myrtales" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="osaensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Conostegia osaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
falls sister to the clade comprised of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia plumosa" order="Myrtales" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="plumosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Conostegia plumosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Naudin" authorityYear="1850" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia speciosa" order="Myrtales" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="speciosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Conostegia speciosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia subcrustulata" order="Myrtales" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subcrustulata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Conostegia subcrustulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia xalapensis" order="Myrtales" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="xalapensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Conostegia xalapensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. With these taxa 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Aguilar, Kriebel &amp; Almeda" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia osaensis" order="Myrtales" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="osaensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Conostegia osaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares the calyptrate calyx and the short style. 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Aguilar, Kriebel &amp; Almeda" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia osaensis" order="Myrtales" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="osaensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Conostegia osaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the largest seeds of any species in 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia" order="Myrtales" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Conostegia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
